From one of the most globally recognised watchmakers Fossil comes this eloquently designed stunner of an analog wristwatch made specifically for women. The timekeeping mechanism on this watch uses the commonly used popular quartz crystal technology which uses small bar shaped crystals of quartz or silicon dioxide.

The biggest advantage of employing this quartz crystal technology is its operational simplicity and accuracy while the entire manufacturing process remains relatively cost effective. With this ultra-fashionable battery powered timekeeping wrist accessory has the right mix of tasteful aesthetics and considerable amount of multi-functionality that is sure to blow you away.

Body and Design

This artistically crafted watch sports a bold round dial that features an extensive amount of stone work around it. This dial that measures 37.5 mm in diameter and 10 mm in thickness has a watch face that carries a light background with a rich and striking mother of pearl finish. This multi-functional watch from Fossil also sports three sub-dials which are given a lighter colour than the watch face and are responsible for tracking other important secondary time-related measurements.

The outermost ring on the dial carries a light coloured track with dark coloured minute markings with corresponding numbering in the standard five minute interval. On the inside of this minute marked track are the hour markers which are small light coloured rectangular bars with a small yet prominent streak of a dark colour infused into it.

All the three watch hands feature a classy soft metallic finish with the hour and the minute hands carrying a significant amount of phosphorescent material. Incorporating the idea of phosphorescence into the dial gives it the advantage of afterglow which in turn lets you easily gauge the time even under low or no light at all.

This multi-functional dial has a considerably thick circle of protection in the form of a stainless steel case. This case features a stainless steel bezel that boasts a ring of semi-precious stones that give the watch a spectacular glitter. The three sub-dials serve the purpose of tracking and indicating the day date and the 24-hour time. The time date and the day can be easily changed with the watch’s rotating crown which is located on the right side of the dial.

This stone-studded dial is kept safely and comfortably attached to your wrist with an immensely stylish stainless steel strap with an 18 mm band width and operates an efficient push button clasp. The dial’s scratch-resistant clear glass cover along with the stainless steel case gives this watch a water-resistance capability of up to 50 m. With such sophistication elegance and functionality this timepiece from Fossil’s analog series makes more of a jewel-laden fashion accessory than just a personal timekeeper.

From one of the most globally recognised watchmakers Fossil comes this eloquently designed stunner of an analog wristwatch made specifically for women. The timekeeping mechanism on this watch uses the commonly used popular quartz crystal technology which uses small bar shaped crystals of quartz or silicon dioxide.

The biggest advantage of employing this quartz crystal technology is its operational simplicity and accuracy while the entire manufacturing process remains relatively cost effective. With this ultra-fashionable battery powered timekeeping wrist accessory has the right mix of tasteful aesthetics and considerable amount of multi-functionality that is sure to blow you away.

Body and Design

This artistically crafted watch sports a bold round dial that features an extensive amount of stone work around it. This dial that measures 37.5 mm in diameter and 10 mm in thickness has a watch face that carries a light background with a rich and striking mother of pearl finish. This multi-functional watch from Fossil also sports three sub-dials which are given a lighter colour than the watch face and are responsible for tracking other important secondary time-related measurements.

The outermost ring on the dial carries a light coloured track with dark coloured minute markings with corresponding numbering in the standard five minute interval. On the inside of this minute marked track are the hour markers which are small light coloured rectangular bars with a small yet prominent streak of a dark colour infused into it.

All the three watch hands feature a classy soft metallic finish with the hour and the minute hands carrying a significant amount of phosphorescent material. Incorporating the idea of phosphorescence into the dial gives it the advantage of afterglow which in turn lets you easily gauge the time even under low or no light at all.

This multi-functional dial has a considerably thick circle of protection in the form of a stainless steel case. This case features a stainless steel bezel that boasts a ring of semi-precious stones that give the watch a spectacular glitter. The three sub-dials serve the purpose of tracking and indicating the day date and the 24-hour time. The time date and the day can be easily changed with the watch’s rotating crown which is located on the right side of the dial.

This stone-studded dial is kept safely and comfortably attached to your wrist with an immensely stylish stainless steel strap with an 18 mm band width and operates an efficient push button clasp. The dial’s scratch-resistant clear glass cover along with the stainless steel case gives this watch a water-resistance capability of up to 50 m. With such sophistication elegance and functionality this timepiece from Fossil’s analog series makes more of a jewel-laden fashion accessory than just a personal timekeeper.
